    <h1 class="mb-4">Privacy Policy – Project Thread</h1>

    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 24th May 2025</p>

    <p>Welcome to <strong>Project Thread</strong>. Your privacy is critically important to us. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our website and services. By accessing or using Project Thread, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.</p>

    <h4>1. Information We Collect</h4>
    <p>We collect several types of information to provide and improve our services.</p>

    <h5>a. Personal Information</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>Full Name</li>
        <li>Email Address</li>
        <li>Phone Number</li>
        <li>Date of Birth</li>
        <li>Gender</li>
        <li>Username</li>
        <li>Password (encrypted)</li>
        <li>IP Address</li>
        <li>Location (if permitted)</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>b. Chat Data</h5>
    <p>We store the messages and interactions you have with other users in our database to provide chat history and support moderation.</p>

    <h5>c. Technical Information</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>Browser type and version</li>
        <li>Operating system</li>
        <li>Referral source</li>
        <li>Date and time of access</li>
        <li>Pages viewed</li>
        <li>Session duration</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>d. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h5>
    <p>We use cookies to personalize content, maintain session state, and analyze user activity.</p>

    <h4>2. How We Use Your Information</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Create and manage your account</li>
        <li>Enable user-to-user chat functionality</li>
        <li>Improve site functionality and user experience</li>
        <li>Provide customer support</li>
        <li>Communicate with you about updates and offers</li>
        <li>Detect and prevent fraud or abuse</li>
        <li>Comply with legal requirements</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>3. Sharing Your Information</h4>
    <p>We do not sell or rent your personal data to third parties. We may share your information only under these circumstances:</p>

    <h5>a. Service Providers</h5>
    <p>We may engage third-party companies to provide services such as hosting, data analytics, or customer support.</p>

    <h5>b. Legal Requirements</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
        <li>Protect and defend our rights or property</li>
        <li>Investigate fraud or misuse</li>
        <li>Protect the safety of users or the public</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>c. Business Transfers</h5>
    <p>If Project Thread is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.</p>

    <h4>4. Data Security</h4>
    <p>We take data security seriously. Measures include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>HTTPS encryption for data transmission</li>
        <li>Password hashing using industry standards</li>
        <li>Limited access to personal information</li>
        <li>Regular server and software updates</li>
    </ul>
    <p>However, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of storage is 100% secure. We strive to use commercially acceptable means but cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

    <h4>5. Data Retention</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Chat data is stored for continuity and support.</li>
        <li>Inactive accounts may be purged after a certain period.</li>
        <li>You may request deletion of your account and data at any time.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>6. Your Rights and Choices</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Access and Correction:</strong> You may access, review, and correct your information through your profile page.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> We can provide a copy of your stored personal data upon request.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Deletion:</strong> You may request the deletion of your account and associated data.</li>
        <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> You can unsubscribe from non-essential communications at any time.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise any of the above rights, please contact us at: <strong>privacy@projectthread.com</strong></p>

    <h4>7. Children’s Privacy</h4>
    <p>Project Thread is not intended for children under the age of 13. If you believe we have collected data from a child under 13, please contact us immediately, and we will take appropriate action.</p>

    <h4>8. Third-Party Links</h4>
    <p>Our platform may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for their content or privacy policies. Please review their privacy statements before providing any information.</p>

    <h4>9. International Users</h4>
    <p>If you are accessing Project Thread from outside your country, your data may be transferred and processed in a jurisdiction that may not have the same data protection laws. By using our services, you consent to this transfer.</p>

    <h4>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h4>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Changes will be posted here with an updated “Effective Date.” Continued use of the service means you accept the revised terms.</p>

